The correct naswer is-&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;Praise&amp;#39;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;let&amp;#39;s look at the meaning of the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;given word&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;and the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;correct answer.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Decried&lt;/span&gt;:&amp;nbsp;to criticize something as bad, without value, or unnecessary (किसी चीज को खराब, बिना मूल्य के, या अनावश्यक के रूप में आलोचना करना)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(48, 51, 54); font-variant-ligatures: no-common-ligatures; letter-spacing: 0.2px;&quot;&gt;​&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(48, 51, 54); font-variant-ligatures: no-common-ligatures; letter-spacing: 0.2px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Lawyers &lt;strong&gt;decried&lt;/strong&gt; the imprisonment of several journalists.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Praise&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 36);&quot;&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;to express admiration or approval of the achievements or characteristics of a person or thing&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 36);&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;(&lt;/span&gt;किसी व्यक्ति या चीज़ की उपलब्धियों या विशेषताओं की प्रशंसा या अनुमोदन व्यक्त करने के लिए&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 36);&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;He should be &lt;strong&gt;praised&lt;/strong&gt; for his honesty.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
		&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Hence, the word&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Praise&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is the most appropriate antonym for&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Decried.&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s explore the meaning of other options&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Criticize&lt;/span&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;to express disapproval of someone or something (किसी की या किसी चीज की अस्वीकृति व्यक्त करना)&amp;nbsp;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;We&amp;#39;ll get nowhere if all you can do is &lt;strong&gt;criticize&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Censure&lt;/span&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;strong criticism or disapproval&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;(कड़ी आलोचना या अस्वीकृति)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;His dishonest behaviour came under severe censure.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Denounce&lt;/span&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;to criticize something or someone strongly and publicly (किसी चीज या किसी की जोरदार और सार्वजनिक रूप से आलोचना करना)&amp;nbsp;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;We must &lt;strong&gt;denounce&lt;/strong&gt; injustice and oppression.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &amp;quot;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rigid&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s look at the meaning of the given word.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pliable&lt;/strong&gt;: &lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;easily bent; flexible.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s look at the meaning of the given options.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Even&lt;/strong&gt;: &lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;flat and smooth.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rigid&lt;/strong&gt;: &lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;unable to bend or be forced out of shape; not flexible.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Smooth&lt;/strong&gt;: having an even and regular surface; free from perceptible projections, lumps, or indentations.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bending&lt;/strong&gt;: &lt;span&gt;shape or force (something straight) into a curve or angle.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;As per the meaning of the given words, &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;rigid&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; is the antonym of the &amp;quot;pliable&amp;quot;.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;em&gt; Aditya&amp;#39;s parents had a &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;rigid &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;point of view regarding love marriage&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hence, the correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; option 2&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/hinglish-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Hinglish&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s look at the meaning of the given word.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pliable&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;span class=&quot;Y2IQFc&quot; lang=&quot;hi&quot;&gt;आसानी से मुड़ा हुआ; लचीला।&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s look at the meaning of the given options.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Even&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;span class=&quot;Y2IQFc&quot; lang=&quot;hi&quot;&gt;सपाट और चिकना।&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rigid&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;span class=&quot;Y2IQFc&quot; lang=&quot;hi&quot;&gt;झुकने या आकार से बाहर होने में असमर्थ; लचीला नहीं।&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Smooth&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;Y2IQFc&quot; lang=&quot;hi&quot;&gt;एक समान और नियमित सतह होना; बोधगम्य अनुमानों, गांठों या खरोजों से मुक्त।&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bending&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;Y2IQFc&quot; lang=&quot;hi&quot;&gt;वक्र या कोण में आकार या बल (कुछ सीधा)।&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;As per the meaning of the given words, &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;rigid&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; is the antonym of the &amp;quot;pliable&amp;quot;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;furious&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;The substitution of&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;extremely angry&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; in one word from the given options is:&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Furious: &lt;/strong&gt;Extremely angry or annoyed.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; She is &lt;strong&gt;furious &lt;/strong&gt;about/at the way she&amp;#39;s been treated.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, from the given meaning and example sentence, &lt;strong&gt;furious &lt;/strong&gt;is the correct one word for &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;extremely angry&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;option 1.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Sentence:&lt;/u&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;My uncle is a colonel who gets &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;furious&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&amp;nbsp;over petty issues every now and then.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s look at the &lt;strong&gt;meaning &lt;/strong&gt;of the other words given in options:-

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fierce &lt;/strong&gt;-&amp;nbsp;having or displaying an intense or ferocious aggressiveness.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Heated &lt;/strong&gt;-&amp;nbsp;inflamed with passion or conviction.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Violent &lt;/strong&gt;-&amp;nbsp;using or involving physical force intended to hurt, damage, or kill someone or something.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Formidable&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Strenuous&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is an adjective which&amp;nbsp;means&amp;nbsp;requiring or using great effort or exertion.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The meaning of the given options are as follows -&amp;nbsp;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Effective&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;-&amp;nbsp;successful in producing a desired or intended result.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Amicable&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;-&amp;nbsp;characterized by friendliness and absence of discord.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Formidable&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;-&amp;nbsp;inspiring fear or respect through being impressively large, powerful, intense, or capable.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Manageable&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;-&amp;nbsp;able to be controlled or dealt with without difficulty.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;From the above meanings it is evident that&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;formidable&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is the correct synonym for the word&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;strenuous&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence, &lt;strong&gt;O&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;ption 3&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;is the correct answer.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;Choreographer&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Choreographer&lt;/span&gt;- a person who creates dance compositions and plans and arranges dance movements and patterns for dances for any program&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:  (34, 41, 45);&quot;&gt;Chauffeur&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;- a person employed to drive a private or hired car&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Director&lt;/span&gt;- a person who is in charge of an activity, department, or organization&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:  (34, 41, 45);&quot;&gt;Calligrapher- &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;a person who is skilled at the art of calligraphy&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let us see the use of the word &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;quot;Choreographer&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt; in a sentence:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Sidhhi is a professional &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Choreographer.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Insufficient.&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Deficient&lt;/strong&gt; means lacking in some essential quality or element. (किसी आवश्यक गुण या तत्व की कमी होना)

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example&lt;/strong&gt;: &lt;em&gt;The company&amp;#39;s budget was &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;deficient,&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt; so they had to cut back on expenses.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Insufficient&lt;/strong&gt; is a synonym of deficient, meaning not enough or inadequate. (अपर्याप्त, नाकाफ़ी)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;The students complained that they were given &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;insufficient&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt; time for the test.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;The correct answer is Option 1.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 2 (Sufficient)&lt;/strong&gt; means enough or adequate, which is the opposite of deficient. (जितना आवश्&amp;zwj;यक हो उतना; पर्याप्त)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 3 (Distinct)&lt;/strong&gt; means clear or easily distinguishable, which is not related to deficient. (स्&amp;zwj;पष्&amp;zwj;ट; सुव्&amp;zwj;यक्त)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 4 (Abundant)&lt;/strong&gt; means plentiful or overflowing, which is the opposite of deficient. (प्रचुर या भरपूर)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Bombastic&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/p&gt;

